{
    "title": "End-to-End Object Detection with Transformers",
    "authors": [
        "Nicolas Carion",
        "Francisco Massa",
        "Gabriel Synnaeve",
        "Nicolas Usunier",
        "Alexander Kirillov",
        "Sergey Zagoruyko"
    ],
    "abstract": "We present a new method that views object detection as a direct set prediction problem. Our approach streamlines the detection pipeline, effectively removing the need for many hand-designed components like a non-maximum suppression procedure or anchor generation that explicitly encode our prior knowledge about the task. The main ingredients of the new framework, called DEtection TRansformer or DETR, are a set-based global loss that forces unique predictions via bipartite matching, and a transformer encoder-decoder architecture. Given a fixed small set of learned object queries, DETR reasons about the relations of the objects and the global image context to directly output the final set of predictions in parallel. The new model is conceptually simple and does not require a specialized library, unlike many other modern detectors. DETR demonstrates accuracy and run-time performance on par with the well-established and highly-optimized Faster R-CNN baseline on the challenging COCO object detection dataset. Moreover, DETR can be easily generalized to produce panoptic segmentation in a unified manner. We show that it significantly outperforms competitive baselines.",
    "summary": "本文提出了一种名为DETR（DEtection TRansformer）的新型目标检测方法，将目标检测视为一个直接的集合预测问题。该方法通过基于二分图匹配的集合全局损失函数和Transformer编码器-解码器架构，简化了检测流程，消除了对非极大值抑制、锚点生成等手工设计组件的需求。DETR利用一组固定的可学习对象查询，并行地直接输出最终预测结果，并在COCO数据集上取得了与高度优化的Faster R-CNN基线相当的精度和运行性能。此外，DETR还能轻松扩展到全景分割任务，并显著优于竞争基线。",
    "keywords": [
        "目标检测",
        "Transformer",
        "集合预测",
        "二分图匹配",
        "端到端学习",
        "注意力机制",
        "全景分割",
        "COCO数据集"
    ],
    "contributions": [
        "提出了一种将目标检测视为直接集合预测问题的新框架DETR，简化了检测流程，无需非极大值抑制和锚点生成等手工设计组件。",
        "设计了一种基于二分图匹配的集合全局损失函数，强制预测与真实目标之间的一一对应，避免重复预测。",
        "采用Transformer编码器-解码器架构，结合自注意力机制，有效建模目标间关系及全局图像上下文，实现并行预测。",
        "在COCO数据集上证明了DETR与高度优化的Faster R-CNN基线相当的精度和运行性能，尤其是在大目标检测上表现更优。",
        "展示了DETR的通用性，通过简单扩展即可应用于全景分割任务，并显著优于竞争基线。"
    ],
    "limitations": [
        "DETR在检测小目标时性能较低，不如Faster R-CNN等基线方法。",
        "训练时间较长，需要超过300个epoch的长时间训练才能达到最佳性能。",
        "模型在编码器中的自注意力计算成本较高，尤其是在使用高分辨率特征图时（如DC5变体），计算量显著增加。",
        "对小目标的检测精度有限，未来可能需要类似特征金字塔网络（FPN）的改进来提升。"
    ],
